Bryson DeChambeau drove the first green and holed the eagle putt during his Sunday singles match against Sergio Garcia at the 2020 Ryder Cup.

Don't miss a moment of the Ryder Cup! Subscribe now: https://www.youtube.com/user/rydercup

The 2020 Ryder Cup takes place at Whistling Straits Golf Course, Wisconsin, United States from 24th - 26th September 2021. Steve Stricker and Padraig Harrington captain the U.S. and European teams respectively. Roughly 40,000 fans are allowed on-site after the event was postponed by a year because of the COVID-19 pandemic. The Ryder Cup has become one of the worldâ€™s greatest sporting events. Every two years, 24 of the best players from Europe and the United States go head-to-head in match play competition. Drama, tension, incredible golf, camaraderie and sportsmanship are served in equal measure, captivating an audience of millions around the world. Itâ€™s an event that transcends sport, yet remains true to the spirit of its founder, Samuel Ryder.
